{"key":"processedPost-11911761","value":{"id":11911761,"first":11908116,"last":11913750,"when":1264623054,"utime":"01/27/10 10:10 PM","content":"Don't put a fluorescent lamp in the FC.&nbsp; It will get hot, and then when you turn it off, it will draw water in as it cools. That's just basic physics.&nbsp; If your lid isn't clear, then put the light on one of the sides, but outside the FC so the heat can exhaust away from your grow.&nbsp; If your whole tub is opaque, get rid of it and pony up ten bucks for a clear one.<br />RR","title":"Re: lights inside monotub"}}